HEADWORD: Lapling
<hw>Lap"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Lap</ets> of a
garment + <ets>ling</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who has been fondled to
excess; one fond of ease and sensual delights; -- a term of
contempt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

